[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish Open: Mark Allen and Joe Swail progress into last 32 in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Antrim player Mark Allen eased to a 4-0 victory over Fang Xiongman in the second round of the Scottish Open.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The world number nine had a highest break of 90 as he brushed aside the challenge of his Chinese opponent at the Emirates Arena in Glasgow.
Allen, who made a maximum 147 in the UK Championship last month, will take on China's Li Hang in the third round.
Belfast's Joe Swail joined Allen in the last 32 by beating Grimsby player Stuart Carrington 4-2.
Swail will next face Australia's 2010 World Champion Neil Robertson.
